    "IntroductionThe installation of renewable energy sources (RES) is crucial to meet the increasing electricity demand.",
    "Wind Energy Conversion Systems (WECS) play a crucial role among different RES, as wind is freely available and abundant; the only cost involved is energy conversion [1].",
    "It is estimated that all countries can generate enough energy needs by installing wind farms on about 2% of their land [2,3].",
    "The basic operating principle of DFIG-based WECS consists of a wound rotor induction generator interfaced with the grid through the stator and rotor ends.",
    "Unlike conventional synchronous generators, where rotor speed and reactive power cannot be controlled, a DFIG uses a back-to-back converter connected to the stator windings."
